# Chapter 4.2 representative security test cases
# This file contains selected manual API tests used for the security analysis
# of the implemented JWT and PASETO authentication prototype.

@gatewayHost = http://localhost:3000
@authHost = http://localhost:3001
@resourceHost = http://localhost:4000

# Valid token placeholders
@jwtAccessToken = REPLACE_WITH_VALID_JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN
@jwtRefreshToken = REPLACE_WITH_VALID_JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN
@pasetoAccessToken = REPLACE_WITH_VALID_PASETO_ACCESS_TOKEN
@pasetoRefreshToken = REPLACE_WITH_VALID_PASETO_REFRESH_TOKEN

# Deliberately modified token placeholders
@tamperedJwtAccessToken = REPLACE_WITH_TAMPERED_JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN
@tamperedPasetoAccessToken = REPLACE_WITH_TAMPERED_PASETO_ACCESS_TOKEN

# Trust-boundary test value
@fakeInternalSecret = attacker-secret

##################################################
### 4.2.1 Access Token Replay
# Purpose: demonstrate that the same valid access token can be reused
# before expiration.
# Coverage: BOTH JWT and PASETO.
# Expected: repeated requests are still accepted while the token remains valid.
##################################################

### JWT replay - first use
GET {{gatewayHost}}/api/jwt-resource/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtAccessToken}}

### JWT replay - second use of the same token
GET {{gatewayHost}}/api/jwt-resource/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtAccessToken}}

### PASETO replay - first use
GET {{gatewayHost}}/api/paseto-resource/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{pasetoAccessToken}}

### PASETO replay - second use of the same token
GET {{gatewayHost}}/api/paseto-resource/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{pasetoAccessToken}}

##################################################
### 4.2.2 Refresh Token Theft, Rotation, and Reuse Detection
# Purpose: show refresh-token rotation and reuse detection.
# Coverage: ONE representative format (JWT).
# Note: the same rotation and reuse-detection logic is applied to both formats.
# Expected:
# - first refresh succeeds and rotates the token
# - second use of the old token is rejected as reuse
##################################################

### JWT refresh - first use of valid refresh token
POST {{gatewayHost}}/api/auth/jwt/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{jwtRefreshToken}}"
}

### JWT refresh - reuse of the old rotated refresh token
POST {{gatewayHost}}/api/auth/jwt/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{jwtRefreshToken}}"
}

##################################################
### 4.2.3 Token Type Misuse
# Purpose: verify that refresh tokens are not accepted where access tokens
# are required.
# Coverage: BOTH JWT and PASETO.
# Expected: the request is rejected because the token type is incorrect.
##################################################

### JWT token-type misuse - refresh token used at protected resource
GET {{gatewayHost}}/api/jwt-resource/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtRefreshToken}}

### PASETO token-type misuse - refresh token used at protected resource
GET {{gatewayHost}}/api/paseto-resource/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{pasetoRefreshToken}}

##################################################
### 4.2.4 Token Tampering and Signature Validation
# Purpose: verify that modified tokens fail verification.
# Coverage: BOTH JWT and PASETO.
# Expected: the request is rejected because signature verification fails.
##################################################

### Tampered JWT access token
GET {{gatewayHost}}/api/jwt-resource/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{tamperedJwtAccessToken}}

### Tampered PASETO access token
GET {{gatewayHost}}/api/paseto-resource/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{tamperedPasetoAccessToken}}

##################################################
### 4.2.5 API Gateway Bypass and Internal Service Access
# Purpose: test trust-boundary enforcement by sending requests directly
# to the Resource Service instead of through the API Gateway.
# Coverage: ONE representative format (JWT).
# Expected: the request is rejected because the internal secret is missing
# or invalid.
##################################################

### Direct access to Resource Service without internal secret
GET {{resourceHost}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtAccessToken}}

### Direct access to Resource Service with fake internal secret
GET {{resourceHost}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtAccessToken}}
x-internal-secret: {{fakeInternalSecret}}

##################################################
### 4.2.6 Endpoint Abuse and Rate Limiting
# Purpose: test gateway rate limiting with repeated authentication requests.
# Coverage: ONE representative format (JWT).
# Expected: after repeated execution, the gateway returns HTTP 429.
# Note: run the request repeatedly until the configured auth limit is exceeded.
##################################################

### Repeated JWT login request for rate-limit testing
POST {{gatewayHost}}/api/auth/jwt/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "rate.limit.test@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword123!"
}

### Repeat
POST {{gatewayHost}}/api/auth/jwt/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "rate.limit.test@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword123!"
}

### Repeat
POST {{gatewayHost}}/api/auth/jwt/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "rate.limit.test@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword123!"
}